3,714 Shares in Elbit Systems Ltd. (NASDAQ:ESLT) Acquired by Caisse DE Depot ET Placement DU Quebec

					Posted by Tristan Rich on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments 




Caisse DE Depot ET Placement DU Quebec acquired a new position in  Elbit Systems Ltd. (NASDAQ:ESLT) during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The institutional investor  acquired 3,714 shares of the aerospace company’s stock, valued at approximately $425,000. 
Other large investors also recently made changes to their positions in the company. Creative Planning raised its stake in shares of  Elbit Systems by 66.7% in the first quarter. Creative Planning now owns 1,000 shares of the aerospace company’s stock worth $114,000 after buying an additional 400 shares during the period.  Bartlett & Co. LLC acquired a new position in  Elbit Systems during the first quarter valued at $114,000.  Westbourne Investment Advisors Inc. acquired a new position in  Elbit Systems during the first quarter valued at $202,000.  US Bancorp DE raised its position in  Elbit Systems by 45.2% in the first quarter. US Bancorp DE now owns 1,835 shares of the aerospace company’s stock valued at $208,000 after buying an additional 571 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, GHP Investment Advisors Inc. acquired a new position in  Elbit Systems during the first quarter valued at $210,000. 10.84% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors. 


 Get Elbit Systems Ltd. alerts:



Shares of Elbit Systems Ltd. (NASDAQ ESLT) traded up 0.13% on Friday, reaching $126.27. The company’s stock had a trading volume of 15,183 shares. Elbit Systems Ltd. has a 52-week low of $91.20 and a 52-week high of $127.97. The company has a 50 day moving average price of $124.77 and a 200 day moving average price of $117.54. The company has a market cap of $5.40 billion, a P/E ratio of 23.44 and a beta of 0.62. 




Elbit Systems (NASDAQ:ESLT) last posted its earnings results on Tuesday, May 16th. The aerospace company reported $1.21 earnings per share for the quarter. Elbit Systems had a net margin of 7.00% and a return on equity of 16.45%. The company had revenue of $749.19 million for the quarter.  On average, analysts anticipate that  Elbit Systems Ltd. will post $6.20 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
